Vice President Pence delivered a commencement address at Grove City College, congratulating the Class of 2017 and emphasizing the importance of leadership. He praised the college for its commitment to independence and principles, noting that it refused federal funding and defended its position before the Supreme Court. Pence encouraged the graduates to be leaders in their respective fields and to inspire others by being people of character. He also emphasized the need for servant leadership and the importance of perseverance in the face of opposition. Pence shared his own journey in public life as an example and urged the graduates to hold onto their dreams. He concluded by urging them to have faith and to trust in God's plans for their lives.